Plus, most states have mandated social distancing to arrest the spread of infection—requirements that would be impossible to adhere to in abortion clinics.
Abortion providers in Texas, led by Planned Parenthood, the nation’s largest abortion provider, filed suit against the state’s decision to restrict abortions under these circumstances.
New York State Attorney General Letitia James was interviewed on National Public Radio to discuss her efforts to organize opposition to efforts to include abortion as a prohibited, nonessential procedure during this crisis.
Per James, New York and 17 other states have filed an amicus brief to support Texas abortion providers’ efforts to restore permissibility of abortion.
As of this writing, there were 123,018 coronavirus cases in New York, amounting to 37% of all cases in the U.S.